{"id":"murmuring","term":"Murmuring","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Of the Hebrews in the wilderness, called forth the displeasure of God, which was only averted by the earnest prayer of Moses (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 11:33\">Num. 11:33</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:3\">34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:12\">12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 15:3\">14:27</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 15:6\">30</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 15:7\">31</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 16:3\">16:3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 21:4\">21:4-6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 106:25\">Ps. 106:25</a>). Forbidden by Paul (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 10:10\">1 Cor. 10:10</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Numbers 11:33","Genesis 2:3","Genesis 1:12","Genesis 15:3","Genesis 15:6","Genesis 15:7","Genesis 16:3","Genesis 21:4","Psalms 106:25","1 Corinthians 10:10"]}